args:
The prince discovers Emile on the run from
some kind of fiend, which they eventually shake
off after reuniting with Leonidas and Chelle.
But flaring tempers and disparate viewpoints
divide the siblings once again, leaving the
prince to fend for himself.
Phew... I've walked so much, but I've seen\nneither hide nor hair of another person.
I guess this island really is deserted. My\nprospects are looking worse by the second.
*pant* *wheeze* What is the MEANING of\nthis?! I am EMPEROR Emile! How dare you\nsubject me to suchâ€”
Eeeek! It's still chasing me! Somebody\nhelp me this INSTANT! I don't care who!
Stop! I have not called for you!\nStay AWAY! Aaaaagh!
{player_name}?! What are YOU\ndoing here?! Wait, no, I don't care.\nJust do something about THAT!
If only it were that easy...
What are you dawdling for? Hurry up\nand lay low my foe, you half-wit!
What do you want me to do, stare it\nto death?! I don't have any weapons.\nAll we can do is run for now!
YIPE! Wait...I know. You stay here as bait!\nThat way, at least I will be able to escape!
Eyagh! Blast it all. What blackguard bars\nmy way NOW?!
AAAGH! Why is that thing so set on\nhaving me for lunch? Can't you even be\nbait properly, you noisome ninny?!
Surely you realize that a fiend of that sort\nwould have a tendency to pursue fleeing\nprey.
Why would I POSSIBLY have knownâ€”AGH!
This is no time for bickering. We have\nto find a way out of this, and quickly!
Right you are, dear Brother.\nFaces down, all three of you!
My eyes! MY EYES! I can't SEE!\nWhat just happened?!
I did warn you to look away. Honestly,\nEmile, you are a walking disaster.
We can ill afford leisurely banter. Quickly,\nflee before the beast's sight is returned!
Hey, wait! I still can't see yet!\nDon't LEAVE MEEE!
Yet the danger remains. Chelle, do you\nstill have any of those flashbombs left?
Alas, that was my only one.
If, perhaps, my luggage has also washed\nashore on this island, I might be able to\ncome up with something...
That's surprisingly uncertain wording\ncoming from you. Are you helpless\nwithout your vaunted network of kittens?

Oh, then perhaps you, with your keen and
penetrating intellect, have a plan? Won't
you please help your dear little sister who
can but speak in uncertainties?
Come on, you two.\nThis is no time to bicker.
I looked around earlier, and I've concluded\nthat we're probably the only four people on\nthis island. We need to work together.
Pah! I'd sooner see my body tossed\nupon the pyre than cooperate with YOU.
I wish you'd see reason, Emile...
So be it. You can sit here twiddling your\nthumbs waiting to die. I will do what I\nmust do to survive.
I will attend to what I must as well.\nBe a dear and secure food and water\nfor us, will you?
Brother, Sister, please, we need to stick\ntogether!
I'm going, too. I have zero desire to\ncontinue on with the likes of YOU!
(I'm sure my friends will rush to my aid\nas soon as they hear that the ship sunk.)
(But we four siblings need to work\ntogether to survive until they get here.)
